  "caveats": [
    "The kill is the strategy MINUS its own always-invested equal-weight buy-and-hold (pure trend-timing). A long-only equity strategy beats the bill on the equity premium, and beats the value-weight market partly on a static equal-weight tilt, so neither is the timing test.",
    "The strategy-minus-value-weight-market difference is reported as deployable context (does this beat holding the market?); the equal-weight-minus-value-weight tilt is the bridge, and strategy-minus-VW equals timing plus tilt by construction.",
